dc:date  a      owl:AnnotationProperty .

gomodel:SYNGO_5350  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 3: Knockdown of PCDH7 changes dendritic spine morphology in dissociated neurons.\n\"Dissociated neurons were transfected with either scrambled shRNA, or two distinct shRNAs targeting PCDH7 (together with GFP as a marker protein), and morphology and density of dendritic spines were analyzed. Neurons with reduced PCDH7 either by shRNA_A or shRNA_C showed similar phenotype with longer dendritic spines (Fig. 3B,C).\n\nWe found that although the total dendritic spine density was not affected by PCDH7 knockdown, there was around 50% reduction in the density of typical spines (length < 2 μm), and about a threefold increase in the density of longer spines (length > 2 μm) (Fig. 3D).\"\n\nFigure 4: Knocking down PCDH7 modestly increases dendritic spine length in hippocampal slices with no significant impact on NMDA current.. Experimental description: \"Primary neuronal culture\nAs described previously46, embryos from timed pregnant Sprague-Dawley rats were removed at E18 and decapitated into cold HBSS/HEPES buffer. The cortex including hippocampus was dissected and placed into 5 mL of HBSS/HEPES buffer.\"\n\nconstructs\n\"Human PCDH7 and PCDH7-GFP were in pRK5 vector; EGFP (GFP), DsRed and rat Pcdh7 were in pCAGGS vector; SHANK3-tdTomato was in pcDNA vector; PCDH7 rat shRNA constructs (both scrambled and targeted) were ordered from Origene.\"\n\nantibody:\n\"PCDH7, Abcam ab139274 clone 2G6, mouse monoclonal mouse antibody used for immunoblot at 1:1,000\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2023-11-08" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_5350" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

